1. extract according version node-v0.10.13-linux-XXX.tar.gz 

way to identify which package to extract:
Open a console and input     uname -a
if there is a X86_64, then use node-v0.10.13-linux-X64.tar.gz,
otherwise, node-v0.10.13-linux-X86.tar.gz

2. rename that extracted folder into node

3. add node binary path to environment

way to add that:
Open a console, go into node/bin folder and input:
export PATH=$PATH:$(pwd)

4. install postgres and create a user kuan with password 123

5. run db.sql(located in my project folder) to build table

6. using 
node app.js in my project root folder(which contain app.js)

7. open browser enter: localhost:3000

